<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Male</emphasis>
(measurements are only from the holotype). BL = 8 mm (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lipotriches (Lipotriches) guihongi Zhang &amp; Niu sp. nov., male a habitus in lateral view b head in frontal view c mesoscutum in dorsal view d propodeum in posterior view e metasoma in dorsal view f metasoma in lateral view g S 5 in dorsal view h genitalia in dorsal view i genitalia in lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (a-f); 0.5 mm (g-i)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.75872.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663097" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">1a</figureCitation>
), body black. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
HL: HW = 0.89, head broader than long (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lipotriches (Lipotriches) guihongi Zhang &amp; Niu sp. nov., male a habitus in lateral view b head in frontal view c mesoscutum in dorsal view d propodeum in posterior view e metasoma in dorsal view f metasoma in lateral view g S 5 in dorsal view h genitalia in dorsal view i genitalia in lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (a-f); 0.5 mm (g-i)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.75872.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663097" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">1b</figureCitation>
); clypeus broader than long (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lipotriches (Lipotriches) guihongi Zhang &amp; Niu sp. nov., male a habitus in lateral view b head in frontal view c mesoscutum in dorsal view d propodeum in posterior view e metasoma in dorsal view f metasoma in lateral view g S 5 in dorsal view h genitalia in dorsal view i genitalia in lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (a-f); 0.5 mm (g-i)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.75872.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663097" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">1b</figureCitation>
); paraocular area with dense large punctures (i = 0.1-0.2d; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lipotriches (Lipotriches) guihongi Zhang &amp; Niu sp. nov., male a habitus in lateral view b head in frontal view c mesoscutum in dorsal view d propodeum in posterior view e metasoma in dorsal view f metasoma in lateral view g S 5 in dorsal view h genitalia in dorsal view i genitalia in lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (a-f); 0.5 mm (g-i)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.75872.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663097" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">1b</figureCitation>
); vertex with sparser large punctures (i = 0.5-1d; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lipotriches (Lipotriches) guihongi Zhang &amp; Niu sp. nov., male a habitus in lateral view b head in frontal view c mesoscutum in dorsal view d propodeum in posterior view e metasoma in dorsal view f metasoma in lateral view g S 5 in dorsal view h genitalia in dorsal view i genitalia in lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (a-f); 0.5 mm (g-i)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.75872.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663097" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">1b</figureCitation>
); vertex behind shiny; posterior margin of vertex rounded (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lipotriches (Lipotriches) guihongi Zhang &amp; Niu sp. nov., male a habitus in lateral view b head in frontal view c mesoscutum in dorsal view d propodeum in posterior view e metasoma in dorsal view f metasoma in lateral view g S 5 in dorsal view h genitalia in dorsal view i genitalia in lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (a-f); 0.5 mm (g-i)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.75872.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663097" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">1a, b</figureCitation>
); mandible blackish-brown; frons with dense and minute punctures, medial frontal line smooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lipotriches (Lipotriches) guihongi Zhang &amp; Niu sp. nov., male a habitus in lateral view b head in frontal view c mesoscutum in dorsal view d propodeum in posterior view e metasoma in dorsal view f metasoma in lateral view g S 5 in dorsal view h genitalia in dorsal view i genitalia in lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (a-f); 0.5 mm (g-i)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.75872.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663097" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">1b</figureCitation>
); antenna reaching the posterior margin of T1; F1-11 almost equal in length, nearly 2.3 times as long as broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lipotriches (Lipotriches) guihongi Zhang &amp; Niu sp. nov., male a habitus in lateral view b head in frontal view c mesoscutum in dorsal view d propodeum in posterior view e metasoma in dorsal view f metasoma in lateral view g S 5 in dorsal view h genitalia in dorsal view i genitalia in lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (a-f); 0.5 mm (g-i)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.75872.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663097" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">1a, b</figureCitation>
); ocelli normal (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lipotriches (Lipotriches) guihongi Zhang &amp; Niu sp. nov., male a habitus in lateral view b head in frontal view c mesoscutum in dorsal view d propodeum in posterior view e metasoma in dorsal view f metasoma in lateral view g S 5 in dorsal view h genitalia in dorsal view i genitalia in lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (a-f); 0.5 mm (g-i)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.75872.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663097" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">1b</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. Mesoscutum, scutellum, and metanotum dull, without reflections (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lipotriches (Lipotriches) guihongi Zhang &amp; Niu sp. nov., male a habitus in lateral view b head in frontal view c mesoscutum in dorsal view d propodeum in posterior view e metasoma in dorsal view f metasoma in lateral view g S 5 in dorsal view h genitalia in dorsal view i genitalia in lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (a-f); 0.5 mm (g-i)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.75872.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663097" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">1c</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum with large and mostly confluent punctures (i = 0.2-0.3d; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Lipotriches (Lipotriches) guihongi Zhang &amp; Niu sp. nov., male a habitus in lateral view b head in frontal view c mesoscutum in dorsal view d propodeum in posterior view e metasoma in dorsal view f metasoma in lateral view g S 5 in dorsal view h genitalia in dorsal view i genitalia in lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (a-f); 0.5 mm (g-i)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.75872.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663097" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">1c</figureCitation>
); metanotum normal, without process, with large punctures which are sparser than punctures on the mesoscutum (Fig. 
